            "text": "Air pollution is the most significant environmental risk factor for all - cause mortality ,",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "and it has caused substantial disability - adjusted life - years and economic loss . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "Air pollution intensified the mortality during past pandemics , Spanish flu in 1918 and SARS - CoV-1 in 2003 . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "It increases host susceptibility and virulence of respiratory infections",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "and reduces viral clearance . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "Thus , a question arises whether there will be any impact of air pollution on the current pandemic coronavirus disease 2019 ( COVID-19 ) ? <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "Thus far , history and science are directing towards an immense potential impact of air pollution on the COVID-19 pandemic . <S>",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "Some of the devastated countries with the current pandemic are those with a poor air quality index . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "Further epidemiological and ecological studies are necessary",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "to confirm this association . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "Also , countries must mobilize funding for mitigation of air pollution",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "to benefit environmental health",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "and ameliorate its potential effects on pandemics of the future . <S> <P>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        }
    ]
